cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically with word embeddings and their biases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves unsupervised learning and evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of biases on sensitive groups, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper uses geometric patterns to identify biases, which could be related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
